#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="dn29"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "dn29:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 29 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 29 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn29:0.2"
msgid "Pāsādikasutta "
msgstr "An Impressive Discourse "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli3.117, sc1
msgctxt "dn29:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn29:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati vedhaññā nāma sakyā, tesaṃ ambavane pāsāde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans in a stilt longhouse in a mango grove belonging to the Sakyan family named Vedhañña. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, pts-vp-pli3.118, sc2
#. VAR: nāṭaputto → nātaputto (bj) | nāthaputto (pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato hoti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta had recently passed away at Pāvā. "

msgctxt "dn29:2.2"
msgid "Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā dvedhikajātā bhaṇḍanajātā kalahajātā vivādāpannā aññamaññaṃ mukhasattīhi vitudantā viharanti: "
msgstr "With his passing the Jain ascetics split, dividing into two factions, arguing, quarreling, and fighting, continually wounding each other with barbed words: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:2.3"
msgid "“na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi? Micchāpaṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammāpaṭipanno. Sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te. Purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca. Adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, niggahito tvamasi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosī”ti. "
msgstr "“You don’t understand this teaching and training. I understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Vadhoyeva kho → vadhoyeveko (mr)
#. VAR: vattati → anuvattati (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:2.4"
msgid "Vadhoyeva kho maññe nigaṇṭhesu nāṭaputtiyesu vattati. "
msgstr "You’d think there was nothing but slaughter going on among the Jain ascetics. "

#. VAR: tepi → te tesu (mr)
#. VAR: nibbinnarūpā → nibiṇṇarūpā (pts1) | nibbindarūpā (mr)
msgctxt "dn29:2.5"
msgid "Yepi nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā, tepi nigaṇṭhesu nāṭaputtiyesu nibbinnarūpā virattarūpā paṭivānarūpā, yathā taṃ durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe. "
msgstr "And the Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta’s white-clothed lay disciples were disillusioned, dismayed, and disappointed in the Jain ascetics. They were equally disappointed with a teaching and training so poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha, with broken monument and without a refuge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, sc3
#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭho → vassaṃ vuttho (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho cundo samaṇuddeso pāvāyaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭho yena sāmagāmo, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho cundo samaṇuddeso āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And then, after completing the rainy season residence near Pāvā, the novice Cunda went to see Venerable Ānanda at Sāma village. He bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "dn29:3.2"
msgid "“nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:3.3"
msgid "Tassa kālaṃkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā dvedhikajātā … pe … bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc4
msgctxt "dn29:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando cundaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Ānanda said to him, "

msgctxt "dn29:4.2"
msgid "“atthi kho idaṃ, āvuso cunda, kathāpābhataṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "“Reverend Cunda, we should see the Buddha about this matter. "

#. VAR: bhagavato ārocessāmā”ti → āroceyyāmāti (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:4.3"
msgid "Āyāmāvuso cunda, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ bhagavato ārocessāmā”ti. "
msgstr "Come, let’s go to the Buddha and tell him about this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho cundo samaṇuddeso āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Cunda. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, sc5
msgctxt "dn29:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ca ānando cundo ca samaṇuddeso yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ānanda and Cunda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

msgctxt "dn29:5.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bhante, cundo samaṇuddeso evamāha, ‘nigaṇṭho, bhante, nāṭaputto pāvāyaṃ adhunākālaṅkato, "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:5.3"
msgid "tassa kālaṅkiriyāya bhinnā nigaṇṭhā … pe … bhinnathūpe appaṭisaraṇe’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:5.4"
msgid "1. Asammāsambuddhappaveditadhammavinaya "
msgstr "1. The Teaching of the Unawakened "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, pts-vp-pli3.119, sc6
msgctxt "dn29:6.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ hetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite. "
msgstr "“That’s what happens, Cunda, when a teaching and training is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:6.2"
msgid "Idha, cunda, satthā ca hoti asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito, "
msgstr "Take the case where a teacher is not awakened, and the teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:6.3"
msgid "sāvako ca tasmiṃ dhamme na dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharati na sāmīcippaṭipanno na anudhammacārī, vokkamma ca tamhā dhammā vattati. "
msgstr "A disciple in that teaching does not practice in line with the teachings, does not practice following that procedure, does not live in line with the teaching. They proceed having turned away from that teaching. "

msgctxt "dn29:6.4"
msgid "So evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should say this to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:6.5"
msgid "‘tassa te, āvuso, lābhā, tassa te suladdhaṃ, "
msgstr "‘You’re fortunate, reverend, you’re so very fortunate! "

msgctxt "dn29:6.6"
msgid "satthā ca te asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "For your teacher is not awakened, and their teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:6.7"
msgid "Tvañca tasmiṃ dhamme na dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharasi, na sāmīcippaṭipanno, na anudhammacārī, vokkamma ca tamhā dhammā vattasī’ti. "
msgstr "But you don’t practice in line with that teaching, you don’t practice following that procedure, you don’t live in line with the teaching. You proceed having turned away from that teaching.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:6.8"
msgid "Iti kho, cunda, satthāpi tattha gārayho, dhammopi tattha gārayho, sāvako ca tattha evaṃ pāsaṃso. "
msgstr "In such a case the teacher and the teaching are to blame, but the disciple deserves praise. "

msgctxt "dn29:6.9"
msgid "Yo kho, cunda, evarūpaṃ sāvakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose someone was to say to such a disciple, "

msgctxt "dn29:6.10"
msgid "‘etāyasmā tathā paṭipajjatu, yathā te satthārā dhammo desito paññatto’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, practice as taught and pointed out by your teacher.’ "

# NOTE: Cp. AN 1.320
msgctxt "dn29:6.11"
msgid "Yo ca samādapeti, yañca samādapeti, yo ca samādapito tathattāya paṭipajjati. Sabbe te bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavanti. "
msgstr "The one who encourages, the one who they encourage, and the one who practices accordingly all make much bad karma. "

msgctxt "dn29:6.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:6.13"
msgid "Evaṃ hetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite. "
msgstr "It’s because that teaching and training is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, pts-vp-pli3.120, sc7
msgctxt "dn29:7.1"
msgid "Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca hoti asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito, "
msgstr "Take the case where a teacher is not awakened, and the teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:7.2"
msgid "sāvako ca tasmiṃ dhamme dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharati sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, samādāya taṃ dhammaṃ vattati. "
msgstr "A disciple in that teaching practices in line with the teachings, practices following that procedure, lives in line with the teaching. They proceed having undertaken that teaching. "

msgctxt "dn29:7.3"
msgid "So evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should say this to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:7.4"
msgid "‘tassa te, āvuso, alābhā, tassa te dulladdhaṃ, satthā ca te asammāsambuddho, dhammo ca durakkhāto duppavedito aniyyāniko anupasamasaṃvattaniko asammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "‘It’s your loss, reverend, it’s your misfortune! For your teacher is not awakened, and their teaching is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:7.5"
msgid "Tvañca tasmiṃ dhamme dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharasi sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, samādāya taṃ dhammaṃ vattasī’ti. "
msgstr "And you practice in line with that teaching, you practice following that procedure, you live in line with the teaching. You proceed having undertaken that teaching.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:7.6"
msgid "Iti kho, cunda, satthāpi tattha gārayho, dhammopi tattha gārayho, sāvakopi tattha evaṃ gārayho. "
msgstr "In such a case the teacher, the teaching, and the disciple are all to blame. "

msgctxt "dn29:7.7"
msgid "Yo kho, cunda, evarūpaṃ sāvakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose someone was to say to such a disciple, "

msgctxt "dn29:7.8"
msgid "‘addhāyasmā ñāyappaṭipanno ñāyamārādhessatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Clearly the venerable is practicing methodically and will succeed in completing that method.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:7.9"
msgid "Yo ca pasaṃsati, yañca pasaṃsati, yo ca pasaṃsito bhiyyoso mattāya vīriyaṃ ārabhati. Sabbe te bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavanti. "
msgstr "The one who praises, the one who they praise, and the one who, being praised, rouses up even more energy all make much bad karma. "

msgctxt "dn29:7.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:7.11"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, cunda, hoti durakkhāte dhammavinaye duppavedite aniyyānike anupasamasaṃvattanike asammāsambuddhappavedite. "
msgstr "It’s because that teaching and training is poorly explained and poorly propounded, not emancipating, not leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is not a fully awakened Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:7.12"
msgid "2. Sammāsambuddhappaveditadhammavinaya "
msgstr "2. The Teaching of the Awakened "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs8, sc8
msgctxt "dn29:8.1"
msgid "Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca hoti sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito, "
msgstr "Take the case where a teacher is awakened, and the teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is a fully awakened Buddha. "

