msgid "So evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should say this to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:8.4"
msgid "‘tassa te, āvuso, alābhā, tassa te dulladdhaṃ, satthā ca te sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "‘It’s your loss, reverend, it’s your misfortune! For your teacher is awakened, and their teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:8.5"
msgid "Tvañca tasmiṃ dhamme na dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharasi, na sāmīcippaṭipanno, na anudhammacārī, vokkamma ca tamhā dhammā vattasī’ti. "
msgstr "But you don’t practice in line with that teaching, you don’t practice following that procedure, you don’t live in line with the teaching. You proceed having turned away from that teaching.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:8.6"
msgid "Iti kho, cunda, satthāpi tattha pāsaṃso, dhammopi tattha pāsaṃso, sāvako ca tattha evaṃ gārayho. "
msgstr "In such a case the teacher and the teaching deserve praise, but the disciple is to blame. "

msgctxt "dn29:8.7"
msgid "Yo kho, cunda, evarūpaṃ sāvakaṃ evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose someone was to say to such a disciple, "

msgctxt "dn29:8.8"
msgid "‘etāyasmā tathā paṭipajjatu yathā te satthārā dhammo desito paññatto’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come on, venerable, practice as taught and pointed out by your teacher.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:8.9"
msgid "Yo ca samādapeti, yañca samādapeti, yo ca samādapito tathattāya paṭipajjati. Sabbe te bahuṃ puññaṃ pasavanti. "
msgstr "The one who encourages, the one who they encourage, and the one who practices accordingly all make much merit. "

msgctxt "dn29:8.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:8.11"
msgid "Evañhetaṃ, cunda, hoti svākkhāte dhammavinaye suppavedite niyyānike upasamasaṃvattanike sammāsambuddhappavedite. "
msgstr "It’s because that teaching and training is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is a fully awakened Buddha. "

