#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:9.13"
msgid "3. Sāvakānutappasatthu "
msgstr "3. When Disciples Have Regrets "

# NOTE: Comm: aviññāpitatthāti abodhitatthā. I think this is a mistake. it is to be understood in line with the Buddha inviting the monks to question him on his deathbed. viññāpita is used in the sense “asked about or for”.
#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs10, pts-vp-pli3.122, sc10
msgctxt "dn29:10.1"
msgid "Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito, "
msgstr "Take the case where a teacher arises in the world who is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.2"
msgid "aviññāpitatthā cassa honti sāvakā saddhamme, na ca tesaṃ kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "But the disciples haven’t inquired about the meaning of that good teaching. And the spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure has not been disclosed and revealed to them with all its collected sayings, with its demonstrable basis, well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.3"
msgid "Atha nesaṃ satthuno antaradhānaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "And then their teacher passes away. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.4"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato anutappo hoti. "
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are tormented by regrets. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:10.6"
msgid "‘Satthā ca no loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho, dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito, aviññāpitatthā camha saddhamme, na ca no kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "They think: ‘Our teacher was perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. His teaching was well explained, but we didn’t inquire about the meaning, and the spiritual practice was not fully disclosed to us. "

msgctxt "dn29:10.7"
msgid "Atha no satthuno antaradhānaṃ hotī’ti. "
msgstr "And then our teacher passed away.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:10.8"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato anutappo hoti. "
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are tormented by regrets. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:10.9"
msgid "4. Sāvakānanutappasatthu "
msgstr "4. When Disciples Have No Regrets "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs11, pts-vp-pli3.123, sc11
msgctxt "dn29:11.1"
msgid "Idha pana, cunda, satthā ca loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho. Dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "Take the case where a teacher arises in the world who is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. The teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.2"
msgid "Viññāpitatthā cassa honti sāvakā saddhamme, kevalañca tesaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "The disciples have inquired about the meaning of that good teaching. And the spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure has been disclosed and revealed to them with all its collected sayings, with its demonstrable basis, well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.3"
msgid "Atha nesaṃ satthuno antaradhānaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "And then their teacher passes away. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.4"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato ananutappo hoti. "
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are free of regrets. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn29:11.6"
msgid "‘Satthā ca no loke udapādi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "They think: ‘Our teacher was perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.7"
msgid "Dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "His teaching was well explained, "

msgctxt "dn29:11.8"
msgid "Viññāpitatthā camha saddhamme, kevalañca no paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ hoti uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "we inquired about the meaning, and the spiritual practice was fully disclosed to us. "

msgctxt "dn29:11.9"
msgid "Atha no satthuno antaradhānaṃ hotī’ti. "
msgstr "And then our teacher passed away.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:11.10"
msgid "Evarūpo kho, cunda, satthā sāvakānaṃ kālaṅkato ananutappo hoti. "
msgstr "When such a teacher has passed away the disciples are free of regrets. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:11.11"
msgid "5. Brahmacariyaaparipūrādikathā "
msgstr "5. On the Incomplete Spiritual Path, Etc. "

# NOTE: Both RD and MW seem to take this as referring to a monk. But it refers to the Buddha, as is made clear in the recapitulation.
#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs12, sc12
msgctxt "dn29:12.1"
msgid "Etehi cepi, cunda, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, no ca kho satthā hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "Now suppose, Cunda, that a spiritual path possesses those factors. But the teacher is not senior, long standing, long gone forth, advanced in years, and reached the final stage of life. "

msgctxt "dn29:12.2"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "Then that spiritual path is incomplete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs13, sc13
msgctxt "dn29:13.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, cunda, etehi ceva aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "But when a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior, "

msgctxt "dn29:13.2"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "then that spiritual path is complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs14, sc14
msgctxt "dn29:14.1"
msgid "Etehi cepi, cunda, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, no ca khvassa therā bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā. "
msgstr "Now suppose that a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior. But there are no senior monk disciples who are competent, educated, assured, have attained sanctuary, "

msgctxt "dn29:14.2"
msgid "Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ. "
msgstr "who can rightly explain the true teaching, and who can legitimately and completely refute the doctrines of others that come up, and teach with a demonstrable basis. "

msgctxt "dn29:14.3"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "Then that spiritual path is incomplete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs15, sc15
msgctxt "dn29:15.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, cunda, etehi ceva aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, therā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā. "
msgstr "But when a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior and there are competent senior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:15.2"
msgid "Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:15.3"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "then that spiritual path is complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs16, pts-vp-pli3.124, sc16
msgctxt "dn29:16.1"
msgid "Etehi cepi, cunda, aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, therā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā. "
msgstr "Now suppose that a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior and there are competent senior monks. "

msgctxt "dn29:16.2"
msgid "Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:16.3"
msgid "No ca khvassa majjhimā bhikkhū sāvakā honti … pe … "
msgstr "But there are no competent middle monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.4"
msgid "majjhimā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti, no ca khvassa navā bhikkhū sāvakā honti … pe … "
msgstr "junior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.5"
msgid "navā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti, no ca khvassa therā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … pe … "
msgstr "senior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.6"
msgid "therā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti, no ca khvassa majjhimā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … pe … "
msgstr "middle nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.7"
msgid "majjhimā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti, no ca khvassa navā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … pe … "
msgstr "junior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.8"
msgid "navā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti, no ca khvassa upāsakā sāvakā honti gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino … pe … "
msgstr "celibate white-clothed laymen, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.9"
msgid "upāsakā cassa sāvakā honti gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, no ca khvassa upāsakā sāvakā honti gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino … pe … "
msgstr "white-clothed laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.10"
msgid "upāsakā cassa sāvakā honti gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino, no ca khvassa upāsikā sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo … pe … "
msgstr "celibate white-clothed laywomen, "

msgctxt "dn29:16.11"
msgid "upāsikā cassa sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo, no ca khvassa upāsikā sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo … pe … "
msgstr "white-clothed laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures. … "

msgctxt "dn29:16.12"
msgid "upāsikā cassa sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo, no ca khvassa brahmacariyaṃ hoti iddhañceva phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "There are white-clothed laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures, but the spiritual path is not successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans … "

msgctxt "dn29:16.13"
msgid "brahmacariyañcassa hoti iddhañceva phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ, no ca kho lābhaggayasaggappattaṃ. "
msgstr "the spiritual path is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans, but it has not reached the peak of material possessions and fame. "

msgctxt "dn29:16.14"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "Then that spiritual path is incomplete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs17, pts-vp-pli3.125, sc17
msgctxt "dn29:17.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, cunda, etehi ceva aṅgehi samannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ hoti, satthā ca hoti thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto, therā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā. "
msgstr "But when a spiritual path possesses those factors and the teacher is senior and there are competent senior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.2"
msgid "Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:17.3"
msgid "Majjhimā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti … "
msgstr "middle monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.4"
msgid "navā cassa bhikkhū sāvakā honti … "
msgstr "junior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.5"
msgid "therā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … "
msgstr "senior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.6"
msgid "majjhimā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … "
msgstr "middle nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.7"
msgid "navā cassa bhikkhuniyo sāvikā honti … "
msgstr "junior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.8"
msgid "upāsakā cassa sāvakā honti … gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino. "
msgstr "celibate laymen, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.9"
msgid "Upāsakā cassa sāvakā honti gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino … "
msgstr "laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.10"
msgid "upāsikā cassa sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo … "
msgstr "celibate laywomen, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.11"
msgid "upāsikā cassa sāvikā honti gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo … "
msgstr "laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.12"
msgid "brahmacariyañcassa hoti iddhañceva phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ, lābhaggappattañca yasaggappattañca. "
msgstr "and the spiritual path is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans, and it has reached the peak of material possessions and fame, "

msgctxt "dn29:17.13"
msgid "Evaṃ taṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ hoti tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "then that spiritual path is complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs18, sc18
msgctxt "dn29:18.1"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana, cunda, etarahi satthā loke uppanno arahaṃ sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "I, Cunda, am a teacher who has arisen in the world today, perfected and fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn29:18.2"
msgid "Dhammo ca svākkhāto suppavedito niyyāniko upasamasaṃvattaniko sammāsambuddhappavedito. "
msgstr "The teaching is well explained and well propounded, emancipating, leading to peace, proclaimed by someone who is fully awakened. "

msgctxt "dn29:18.3"
msgid "Viññāpitatthā ca me sāvakā saddhamme, kevalañca tesaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ āvikataṃ uttānīkataṃ sabbasaṅgāhapadakataṃ sappāṭihīrakataṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "My disciples have inquired about the meaning of that good teaching. And the spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure has been disclosed and revealed to them with all its collected sayings, with its demonstrable basis, well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn29:18.4"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana, cunda, etarahi satthā thero rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "I am a teacher today who is senior, long standing, long gone forth, advanced in years, and have reached the final stage of life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs19, pts-vp-pli3.126, sc19
msgctxt "dn29:19.1"
msgid "Santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi therā bhikkhū sāvakā honti viyattā vinītā visāradā pattayogakkhemā. "
msgstr "I have today disciples who are competent senior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.2"
msgid "Alaṃ samakkhātuṃ saddhammassa, alaṃ uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammehi suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desetuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:19.3"
msgid "Santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi majjhimā bhikkhū sāvakā … "
msgstr "middle monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.4"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi navā bhikkhū sāvakā … "
msgstr "junior monks, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.5"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi therā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā … "
msgstr "senior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.6"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi majjhimā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā … "
msgstr "middle nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.7"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi navā bhikkhuniyo sāvikā … "
msgstr "junior nuns, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.8"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi upāsakā sāvakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino … "
msgstr "celibate laymen, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.9"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi upāsakā sāvakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino … "
msgstr "laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.10"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi upāsikā sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo … "
msgstr "celibate laywomen, "

msgctxt "dn29:19.11"
msgid "santi kho pana me, cunda, etarahi upāsikā sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo … "
msgstr "and laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "dn29:19.12"
msgid "etarahi kho pana me, cunda, brahmacariyaṃ iddhañceva phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ. "
msgstr "Today my spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs20, sc20
msgctxt "dn29:20.1"
msgid "Yāvatā kho, cunda, etarahi satthāro loke uppannā, nāhaṃ, cunda, aññaṃ ekasatthārampi samanupassāmi evaṃlābhaggayasaggappattaṃ yatharivāhaṃ. "
msgstr "Of all the teachers in the world today, Cunda, I don’t see even a single one who has reached the peak of material possessions and fame like me. "

msgctxt "dn29:20.2"
msgid "Yāvatā kho pana, cunda, etarahi saṅgho vā gaṇo vā loke uppanno; "
msgstr "Of all the spiritual communities and groups in the world today, Cunda, I don’t see even a single one who has reached the pinnacle of material possessions and fame like the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn29:20.3"
msgid "nāhaṃ, cunda, aññaṃ ekasaṅghampi samanupassāmi evaṃlābhaggayasaggappattaṃ yatharivāyaṃ, cunda, bhikkhusaṅgho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:20.4"
msgid "Yaṃ kho taṃ, cunda, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "And if there’s any spiritual path of which it may be rightly said that "

msgctxt "dn29:20.5"
msgid "‘sabbākārasampannaṃ sabbākāraparipūraṃ anūnamanadhikaṃ svākkhātaṃ kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ suppakāsitan’ti. "
msgstr "it’s endowed with all good qualities, complete in all good qualities, neither too little nor too much, well explained, whole, full, and well propounded, "

msgctxt "dn29:20.6"
msgid "Idameva taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "it’s of this spiritual path that this should be said. "

msgctxt "dn29:20.7"
msgid "‘sabbākārasampannaṃ … pe … suppakāsitan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs21, pts-vp-pli3.127, sc21
#. VAR: Udako → uddako (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:21.1"
msgid "Udako sudaṃ, cunda, rāmaputto evaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati: "
msgstr "Uddaka, son of Rāma, used to say: "

msgctxt "dn29:21.2"
msgid "‘passaṃ na passatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Seeing, one does not see.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:21.3"
msgid "Kiñca passaṃ na passatīti? "
msgstr "But seeing what does one not see? "

#. VAR: na passati → na passatīti (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:21.4"
msgid "Khurassa sādhunisitassa talamassa passati, dhārañca khvassa na passati. "
msgstr "You can see the blade of a well-sharpened razor, but not the edge. "

msgctxt "dn29:21.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati: "
msgstr "Thus it is said: "

msgctxt "dn29:21.6"
msgid "‘passaṃ na passatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Seeing, one does not see.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:21.7"
msgid "Yaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, udakena rāmaputtena bhāsitaṃ hīnaṃ gammaṃ pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ khurameva sandhāya. "
msgstr "But that saying of Uddaka’s is low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless, as it’s only concerning a razor. "

#. VAR: Yañca taṃ → yañcetaṃ (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:21.8"
msgid "Yañca taṃ, cunda, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "If there’s anything of which it may be rightly said: "

#. VAR: idameva taṃ → idamevetaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:21.9"
msgid "‘passaṃ na passatī’ti, idameva taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr "‘Seeing, one does not see,’ it’s of this that it should be said. "

msgctxt "dn29:21.10"
msgid "‘passaṃ na passatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:21.11"
msgid "Kiñca passaṃ na passatīti? "
msgstr "Seeing what does one not see? "

#. VAR: paripūraṃ → pari­suddha­taraṃ (bj, s1-3, mr) | paripūrataraṃ (?)
#. VAR: hetaṃ passati → na passatīti (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn29:21.12"
msgid "Evaṃ sabbākārasampannaṃ sabbākāraparipūraṃ anūnamanadhikaṃ svākkhātaṃ kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ suppakāsitanti, iti hetaṃ passati. "
msgstr "One sees this: a spiritual path endowed with all good qualities, complete in all good qualities, neither too little nor too much, well explained, whole, full, and well propounded. "

msgctxt "dn29:21.13"
msgid "Idamettha apakaḍḍheyya, evaṃ taṃ parisuddhataraṃ assāti, iti hetaṃ na passati. "
msgstr "One does not see this: anything that, were it to be removed, would make it purer. "

msgctxt "dn29:21.14"
msgid "Idamettha upakaḍḍheyya, evaṃ taṃ paripūraṃ assāti, iti hetaṃ na passati. "
msgstr "One does not see this: anything that, were it to be added, would make it more complete. "

msgctxt "dn29:21.15"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, cunda: "
msgstr "Thus it is rightly said: "

msgctxt "dn29:21.16"
msgid "‘passaṃ na passatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Seeing, one does not see.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:21.17"
msgid "Yaṃ kho taṃ, cunda, sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:21.18"
msgid "‘sabbākārasampannaṃ … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:21.19"
msgid "brahmacariyaṃ suppakāsitan’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:21.20"
msgid "Idameva taṃ sammā vadamāno vadeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:21.21"
msgid "‘sabbākārasampannaṃ sabbākāraparipūraṃ anūnamanadhikaṃ svākkhātaṃ kevalaṃ paripūraṃ brahmacariyaṃ suppakāsitan’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:21.22"
msgid "6. Saṅgāyitabbadhamma "
msgstr "6. Teachings Should be Recited in Concert "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs22, pts-vp-pli3.128, sc22
msgctxt "dn29:22.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, cunda, ye vo mayā dhammā abhiññā desitā, tattha sabbeheva saṅgamma samāgamma atthena atthaṃ byañjanena byañjanaṃ saṅgāyitabbaṃ na vivaditabbaṃ, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr "So, Cunda, you should all come together and recite in concert, without disputing, those things I have taught you from my direct knowledge, comparing meaning with meaning and phrasing with phrasing, so that this spiritual path may last for a long time. That would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans. "

msgctxt "dn29:22.2"
msgid "Katame ca te, cunda, dhammā mayā abhiññā desitā, yattha sabbeheva saṅgamma samāgamma atthena atthaṃ byañjanena byañjanaṃ saṅgāyitabbaṃ na vivaditabbaṃ, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ? "
msgstr "And what are those things I have taught from my direct knowledge? "

msgctxt "dn29:22.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro iddhipādā, pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo. "
msgstr "They are the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right efforts, the four bases of psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven awakening factors, and the noble eightfold path. "

msgctxt "dn29:22.4"
msgid "Ime kho te, cunda, dhammā mayā abhiññā desitā. "
msgstr "These are the things I have taught from my own direct knowledge. "

msgctxt "dn29:22.5"
msgid "Yattha sabbeheva saṅgamma samāgamma atthena atthaṃ byañjanena byañjanaṃ saṅgāyitabbaṃ na vivaditabbaṃ, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:22.6"
msgid "7. Saññāpetabbavidhi "
msgstr "7. Reaching Agreement "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs23, sc23
#. VAR: sikkhataṃ → sikkhitabbaṃ (bahūsu)
msgctxt "dn29:23.1"
msgid "Tesañca vo, cunda, samaggānaṃ sammodamānānaṃ avivadamānānaṃ sikkhataṃ aññataro sabrahmacārī saṃghe dhammaṃ bhāseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose one of those spiritual companions who is training in harmony and mutual appreciation, without fighting, were to recite the teaching in the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn29:23.2"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

#. VAR: ceva → yo ceva (s1-3, pts1) | yañceva (mr)
msgctxt "dn29:23.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā atthañceva micchā gaṇhāti, byañjanāni ca micchā ropetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This venerable misconstrues the meaning and mistakes the phrasing.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:23.4"
msgid "Tassa neva abhinanditabbaṃ na paṭikkositabbaṃ, anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss them, but say, "

#. VAR: imesañca → imesaṃ (sabbattha)
msgctxt "dn29:23.5"
msgid "‘imassa nu kho, āvuso, atthassa imāni vā byañjanāni etāni vā byañjanāni katamāni opāyikatarāni, imesañca byañjanānaṃ ayaṃ vā attho eso vā attho katamo opāyikataro’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, if this is the meaning, the phrasing may either be this or that: which is more fitting? And if this is the phrasing, the meaning may be either this or that: which is more fitting?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:23.6"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose they reply, "

msgctxt "dn29:23.7"
msgid "‘imassa kho, āvuso, atthassa imāneva byañjanāni opāyikatarāni, yā ceva etāni; imesañca byañjanānaṃ ayameva attho opāyikataro, yā ceva eso’ti. "
msgstr "‘This phrasing fits the meaning better than that. And this meaning fits the phrasing better than that.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:23.8"
msgid "So neva ussādetabbo na apasādetabbo, anussādetvā anapasādetvā sveva sādhukaṃ saññāpetabbo tassa ca atthassa tesañca byañjanānaṃ nisantiyā. "
msgstr "Without flattering or rebuking them, you should carefully convince them by examining that meaning and that phrasing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs24, pts-vp-pli3.129, sc24
msgctxt "dn29:24.1"
msgid "Aparopi ce, cunda, sabrahmacārī saṅghe dhammaṃ bhāseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose another spiritual companion were to recite the teaching in the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn29:24.2"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

msgctxt "dn29:24.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā atthañhi kho micchā gaṇhāti byañjanāni sammā ropetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This venerable misconstrues the meaning but gets the phrasing right.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:24.4"
msgid "Tassa neva abhinanditabbaṃ na paṭikkositabbaṃ, anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss them, but say, "

msgctxt "dn29:24.5"
msgid "‘imesaṃ nu kho, āvuso, byañjanānaṃ ayaṃ vā attho eso vā attho katamo opāyikataro’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, if this is the phrasing, the meaning may be either this or that: which is more fitting?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:24.6"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose they reply, "

msgctxt "dn29:24.7"
msgid "‘imesaṃ kho, āvuso, byañjanānaṃ ayameva attho opāyikataro, yā ceva eso’ti. "
msgstr "‘This meaning fits the phrasing better than that.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:24.8"
msgid "So neva ussādetabbo na apasādetabbo, anussādetvā anapasādetvā sveva sādhukaṃ saññāpetabbo tasseva atthassa nisantiyā. "
msgstr "Without flattering or rebuking, you should carefully convince them by examining that meaning. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs25, sc25
msgctxt "dn29:25.1"
msgid "Aparopi ce, cunda, sabrahmacārī saṅghe dhammaṃ bhāseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose another spiritual companion were to recite the teaching in the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn29:25.2"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

msgctxt "dn29:25.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā atthañhi kho sammā gaṇhāti byañjanāni micchā ropetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This venerable construes the meaning correctly but mistakes the phrasing.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:25.4"
msgid "Tassa neva abhinanditabbaṃ na paṭikkositabbaṃ; anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss them, but say, "

msgctxt "dn29:25.5"
msgid "‘imassa nu kho, āvuso, atthassa imāni vā byañjanāni etāni vā byañjanāni katamāni opāyikatarānī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, if this is the meaning, the phrasing may be either this or that: which is more fitting?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:25.6"
msgid "So ce evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Suppose they reply, "

msgctxt "dn29:25.7"
msgid "‘imassa kho, āvuso, atthassa imāneva byañjanāni opayikatarāni, yā ceva etānī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This phrasing fits the meaning better than that.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:25.8"
msgid "So neva ussādetabbo na apasādetabbo; anussādetvā anapasādetvā sveva sādhukaṃ saññāpetabbo tesaññeva byañjanānaṃ nisantiyā. "
msgstr "Without flattering or rebuking, you should carefully convince them by examining that phrasing. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs26, sc26
msgctxt "dn29:26.1"
msgid "Aparopi ce, cunda, sabrahmacārī saṅghe dhammaṃ bhāseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose another spiritual companion were to recite the teaching in the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn29:26.2"
msgid "Tatra ce tumhākaṃ evamassa: "
msgstr "Now, you might think, "

msgctxt "dn29:26.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā atthañceva sammā gaṇhāti byañjanāni ca sammā ropetī’ti. "
msgstr "‘This venerable construes the meaning correctly and gets the phrasing right.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:26.4"
msgid "Tassa ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditabbaṃ anumoditabbaṃ; "
msgstr "Saying ‘Good!’ you should applaud and cheer that mendicant’s statement, "

msgctxt "dn29:26.5"
msgid "tassa ‘sādhū’ti bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā so evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "and then say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:26.6"
msgid "‘lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, "
msgstr "‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "dn29:26.7"
msgid "ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma evaṃ atthupetaṃ byañjanupetan’ti. "
msgstr "to see a venerable such as yourself, so well-versed in the meaning and the phrasing, as one of our spiritual companions!’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:26.8"
msgid "8. Paccayānuññātakāraṇa "
msgstr "8. The Reasons for Allowing Requisites "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs27, pts-vp-pli3.130, sc27
msgctxt "dn29:27.1"
msgid "Na vo ahaṃ, cunda, diṭṭhadhammikānaṃyeva āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "Cunda, I do not teach you solely for restraining defilements that affect the present life. "

msgctxt "dn29:27.2"
msgid "Na panāhaṃ, cunda, samparāyikānaṃyeva āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "Nor do I teach solely for protecting against defilements that affect lives to come. "

msgctxt "dn29:27.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ cevāhaṃ, cunda, āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya dhammaṃ desemi; "
msgstr "I teach both for restraining defilements that affect the present life and "

#. VAR: ca → cāti (bahūsu)
msgctxt "dn29:27.4"
msgid "samparāyikānañca āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya. "
msgstr "protecting against defilements that affect lives to come. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Both MW and RD have optative mod here, but it is not justified.
msgctxt "dn29:27.5"
msgid "Tasmātiha, cunda, yaṃ vo mayā cīvaraṃ anuññātaṃ, alaṃ vo taṃ "
msgstr "And that’s why I have allowed robes for you that suffice "

msgctxt "dn29:27.6"
msgid "yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva hirikopīnapaṭicchādanatthaṃ. "
msgstr "only for the sake of warding off cold and heat; for warding off the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; and for covering up the private parts. "

msgctxt "dn29:27.7"
msgid "Yo vo mayā piṇḍapāto anuññāto, alaṃ vo so "
msgstr "I have allowed alms-food for you that suffices "

msgctxt "dn29:27.8"
msgid "yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro ca. "
msgstr "only to continue and sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice; so that you will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and will keep on living blamelessly and at ease. "

msgctxt "dn29:27.9"
msgid "Yaṃ vo mayā senāsanaṃ anuññātaṃ, alaṃ vo taṃ "
msgstr "I have allowed lodgings for you that suffice "

msgctxt "dn29:27.10"
msgid "yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva utuparissayavinodanapaṭisallānārāmatthaṃ. "
msgstr "only for the sake of warding off cold and heat; for warding off the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; to shelter from harsh weather and to enjoy retreat. "

msgctxt "dn29:27.11"
msgid "Yo vo mayā gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāro anuññāto, alaṃ vo so "
msgstr "I have allowed medicines and supplies for the sick for you that suffice "

msgctxt "dn29:27.12"
msgid "yāvadeva uppannānaṃ veyyābādhikānaṃ vedanānaṃ paṭighātāya abyāpajjaparamatāya. "
msgstr "only for the sake of warding off the pains of illness and to promote good health. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:27.13"
msgid "9. Sukhallikānuyoga "
msgstr "9. Indulgence in Pleasure "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs28, sc28
msgctxt "dn29:28.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:28.2"
msgid "‘sukhallikānuyogamanuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure.’ "

#. VAR: Evaṃvādino → … vadamānā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:28.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:28.4"
msgid "‘katamo so, āvuso, sukhallikānuyogo? "
msgstr "‘What is that indulgence in pleasure? "

msgctxt "dn29:28.5"
msgid "Sukhallikānuyogā hi bahū anekavihitā nānappakārakā’ti. "
msgstr "For there are many different kinds of indulgence in pleasure.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs29, sc29
msgctxt "dn29:29.1"
msgid "Cattārome, cunda, sukhallikānuyogā hīnā gammā pothujjanikā anariyā anatthasaṃhitā na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These four kinds of indulgence in pleasure, Cunda, are low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

msgctxt "dn29:29.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs30, sc30
msgctxt "dn29:30.1"
msgid "Idha, cunda, ekacco bālo pāṇe vadhitvā vadhitvā attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti. "
msgstr "It’s when some fool makes themselves happy and pleased by killing living creatures. "

msgctxt "dn29:30.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the first kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs31, pts-vp-pli3.131, sc31
msgctxt "dn29:31.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco adinnaṃ ādiyitvā ādiyitvā attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, someone makes themselves happy and pleased by theft. "

msgctxt "dn29:31.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the second kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs32, sc32
msgctxt "dn29:32.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco musā bhaṇitvā bhaṇitvā attānaṃ sukheti pīṇeti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, someone makes themselves happy and pleased by lying. "

msgctxt "dn29:32.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the third kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs33, sc33
msgctxt "dn29:33.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, idhekacco pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, someone amuses themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation. "

msgctxt "dn29:33.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs34, sc34
msgctxt "dn29:34.1"
msgid "Ime kho, cunda, cattāro sukhallikānuyogā hīnā gammā pothujjanikā anariyā anatthasaṃhitā na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of indulgence in pleasure that are low, crude, ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs35, sc35
msgctxt "dn29:35.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

# NOTE: RD and MW phrase this as a question, which is unjustified.
msgctxt "dn29:35.2"
msgid "‘ime cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure in these four ways.’ "

#. VAR: vo → te (pts1)
msgctxt "dn29:35.3"
msgid "Te vo ‘mā hevaṃ’ tissu vacanīyā. "
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Not so!’ "

msgctxt "dn29:35.4"
msgid "Na te vo sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ, abbhācikkheyyuṃ asatā abhūtena. "
msgstr "It isn’t right to say that about you; it misrepresents you with an untruth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs36, sc36
msgctxt "dn29:36.1"
msgid "Cattārome, cunda, sukhallikānuyogā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These four kinds of indulgence in pleasure, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

msgctxt "dn29:36.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs37, sc37
msgctxt "dn29:37.1"
msgid "Idha, cunda, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn29:37.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the first kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs38, sc38
msgctxt "dn29:38.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption. It has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "dn29:38.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the second kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs39, sc39
msgctxt "dn29:39.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption. They meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:39.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the third kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs40, pts-vp-pli3.132, sc40
msgctxt "dn29:40.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, cunda, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption. It is without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "dn29:40.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho sukhallikānuyogo. "
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of indulgence in pleasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs41, sc41
msgctxt "dn29:41.1"
msgid "Ime kho, cunda, cattāro sukhallikānuyogā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of indulgence in pleasure which, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs42, sc42
msgctxt "dn29:42.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:42.2"
msgid "‘ime cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan live indulging in pleasure in these four ways.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:42.3"
msgid "Te vo ‘evaṃ’ tissu vacanīyā. "
msgstr "They should be told, ‘Exactly so!’ "

msgctxt "dn29:42.4"
msgid "Sammā te vo vadamānā vadeyyuṃ, na te vo abbhācikkheyyuṃ asatā abhūtena. "
msgstr "It’s right to say that about you; it doesn’t misrepresent you with an untruth. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:42.5"
msgid "10. Sukhallikānuyogānisaṃsa "
msgstr "10. The Benefits of Indulgence in Pleasure "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs43, sc43
msgctxt "dn29:43.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:43.2"
msgid "‘ime panāvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ kati phalāni katānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā’ti? "
msgstr "‘How many fruits and benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in pleasure in these four ways?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:43.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:43.4"
msgid "‘ime kho, āvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ cattāri phalāni cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā. "
msgstr "‘Four benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in pleasure in these four ways. "

msgctxt "dn29:43.5"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:43.6"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo. "
msgstr "Firstly, with the ending of three fetters a mendicant becomes a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening. "

msgctxt "dn29:43.7"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ phalaṃ, paṭhamo ānisaṃso. "
msgstr "This is the first fruit and benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:43.8"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant—with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion—becomes a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. "

msgctxt "dn29:43.9"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ phalaṃ, dutiyo ānisaṃso. "
msgstr "This is the second fruit and benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:43.10"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "Furthermore, with the ending of the five lower fetters, a mendicant is reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

msgctxt "dn29:43.11"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ phalaṃ, tatiyo ānisaṃso. "
msgstr "This is the third fruit and benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:43.12"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, āvuso, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "dn29:43.13"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ phalaṃ catuttho ānisaṃso. "
msgstr "This is the fourth fruit and benefit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:43.14"
msgid "Ime kho, āvuso, cattāro sukhallikānuyoge anuyuttānaṃ viharataṃ imāni cattāri phalāni, cattāro ānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā’ti. "
msgstr "These four benefits may be expected by those who live indulging in pleasure in these four ways.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:43.15"
msgid "11. Khīṇāsavaabhabbaṭhāna "
msgstr "11. Things Impossible for the Perfected "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs44, pts-vp-pli3.133, sc44
msgctxt "dn29:44.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

# NOTE: Both RD and MW take dhamma in (at)thitadhamma here as “doctrine”, but it is at AN 8.19 in the same context, but of the ocean, where it just means “stable”. Both places are glossed as ṭhitasabhāvā. Incidentally, the context here shows that PTS dict’s “eternal” for AN 8.19 is wrong.
msgctxt "dn29:44.2"
msgid "‘aṭṭhitadhammā samaṇā sakyaputtiyā viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetics who follow the Sakyan are inconsistent.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:44.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:44.4"
msgid "‘atthi kho, āvuso, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā paññattā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyā. "
msgstr "‘Reverends, these things have been taught and pointed out for his disciples by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, not to be transgressed so long as life lasts. "

msgctxt "dn29:44.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, indakhīlo vā ayokhīlo vā gambhīranemo sunikhāto acalo asampavedhī; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a boundary pillar or an iron pillar with deep foundations, firmly embedded, imperturbable and unshakable. "

msgctxt "dn29:44.6"
msgid "evameva kho, āvuso, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sāvakānaṃ dhammā desitā paññattā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyā. "
msgstr "In the same way, these things have been taught and pointed out for his disciples by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, not to be transgressed so long as life lasts. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:44.7"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so nava ṭhānāni ajjhācarituṃ. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—can’t transgress in nine respects. "

msgctxt "dn29:44.8"
msgid "Abhabbo, āvuso, khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropetuṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyituṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevituṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sampajānamusā bhāsituṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ kāme paribhuñjituṃ, seyyathāpi pubbe āgārikabhūto; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu chandāgatiṃ gantuṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu dosāgatiṃ gantuṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu mohāgatiṃ gantuṃ; abhabbo khīṇāsavo bhikkhu bhayāgatiṃ gantuṃ. "
msgstr "A mendicant with defilements ended can’t deliberately take the life of a living creature, take something with the intention to steal, have sex, tell a deliberate lie, or store up goods for their own enjoyment like they did as a lay person. And they can’t make decisions prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, or cowardice. "

msgctxt "dn29:44.9"
msgid "Yo so, āvuso, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, abhabbo so imāni nava ṭhānāni ajjhācaritun’ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant who is perfected can’t transgress in these nine respects.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:44.10"
msgid "12. Pañhābyākaraṇa "
msgstr "12. Questions and Answers "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs45, pts-vp-pli3.134, sc45
msgctxt "dn29:45.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:45.2"
msgid "‘atītaṃ kho addhānaṃ ārabbha samaṇo gotamo atīrakaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapeti, no ca kho anāgataṃ addhānaṃ ārabbha atīrakaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapeti, tayidaṃ kiṃsu tayidaṃ kathaṃsū’ti? "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama demonstrates boundless knowledge and vision of the past, but not of the future. What’s up with that?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:45.3"
msgid "Te ca aññatitthiyā paribbājakā aññavihitakena ñāṇadassanena aññavihitakaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ paññapetabbaṃ maññanti yathariva bālā abyattā. "
msgstr "Those wanderers, like incompetent fools, seem to imagine that one kind of knowledge and vision can be demonstrated by means of another kind of knowledge and vision. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:45.4"
msgid "Atītaṃ kho, cunda, addhānaṃ ārabbha tathāgatassa satānusāriñāṇaṃ hoti; "
msgstr "Regarding the past, the Realized One has knowledge stemming from memory. "

msgctxt "dn29:45.5"
msgid "so yāvatakaṃ ākaṅkhati tāvatakaṃ anussarati. "
msgstr "He recollects as far as he wants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:45.6"
msgid "Anāgatañca kho addhānaṃ ārabbha tathāgatassa bodhijaṃ ñāṇaṃ uppajjati: "
msgstr "Regarding the future, the Realized One has the knowledge born of awakening: "

msgctxt "dn29:45.7"
msgid "‘ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is my last rebirth. Now there are no more future lives.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:45.8"
msgid "Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ tathāgato byākaroti. "
msgstr "If a question about the past is untrue, false, and pointless, the Realized One does not reply. "

msgctxt "dn29:45.9"
msgid "Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, tampi tathāgato na byākaroti. "
msgstr "If a question about the past is true and substantive, but pointless, he does not reply. "

msgctxt "dn29:45.10"
msgid "Atītañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ, tatra kālaññū tathāgato hoti tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya. "
msgstr "If a question about the past is true, substantive, and beneficial, he knows the right time to reply. "

msgctxt "dn29:45.11"
msgid "Anāgatañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ tathāgato byākaroti … pe … tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya. "
msgstr "And the Realized One replies to questions about the future or the present in the same way. "

msgctxt "dn29:45.12"
msgid "Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti abhūtaṃ atacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na taṃ tathāgato byākaroti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:45.13"
msgid "Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, tampi tathāgato na byākaroti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn29:45.14"
msgid "Paccuppannañcepi, cunda, hoti bhūtaṃ tacchaṃ atthasaṃhitaṃ, tatra kālaññū tathāgato hoti tassa pañhassa veyyākaraṇāya. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs46, sc46
#. VAR: tathāgato kālavādī → kālavādī saccavādī (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn29:46.1"
msgid "Iti kho, cunda, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu dhammesu tathāgato kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "And so the Realized One has speech that’s well-timed, true, meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:46.2"
msgid "Yañca kho, cunda, sadevakassa lokassa samārakassa sabrahmakassa sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, sabbaṃ tathāgatena abhisambuddhaṃ, "
msgstr "In this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—whatever is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind, all that has been understood by the Realized One. "

msgctxt "dn29:46.3"
msgid "tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:46.4"
msgid "Yañca, cunda, rattiṃ tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhati, yañca rattiṃ anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyati, yaṃ etasmiṃ antare bhāsati lapati niddisati. Sabbaṃ taṃ tatheva hoti no aññathā, "
msgstr "From the night when the Realized One understands the supreme perfect awakening until the night he becomes fully extinguished—through the natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over—everything he speaks, says, and expresses is real, not otherwise. "

msgctxt "dn29:46.5"
msgid "tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "That’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn29:46.6"
msgid "Yathāvādī, cunda, tathāgato tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī. "
msgstr "The Realized One does as he says, and says as he does. "

msgctxt "dn29:46.7"
msgid "Iti yathāvādī tathākārī, yathākārī tathāvādī, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "Since this is so, that’s why he’s called the ‘Realized One’. "

msgctxt "dn29:46.8"
msgid "Sadevake loke, cunda, samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya tathāgato abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī, tasmā ‘tathāgato’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "In this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—the Realized One is the undefeated, the champion, the universal seer, the wielder of power. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:46.9"
msgid "13. Abyākataṭṭhāna "
msgstr "13. The Undeclared Points "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs47, pts-vp-pli3.136, sc47
msgctxt "dn29:47.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:47.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is this your view: “A Realized One exists after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly”?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:47.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:47.4"
msgid "‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "‘Reverend, this has not been declared by the Buddha.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:47.5"
msgid "“hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs48, sc48
msgctxt "dn29:48.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "The wanderers might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:48.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāvuso, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Then is this your view: “A Realized One doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly”?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:48.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:48.4"
msgid "‘etampi kho, āvuso, bhagavatā abyākataṃ: "
msgstr "‘This too has not been declared by the Buddha.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:48.5"
msgid "“na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs49, sc49
msgctxt "dn29:49.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "The wanderers might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:49.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāvuso, hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Then is this your view: “A Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly”?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:49.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:49.4"
msgid "‘abyākataṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "‘This too has not been declared by the Buddha.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:49.5"
msgid "“hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs50, sc50
msgctxt "dn29:50.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "The wanderers might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:50.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāvuso, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Then is this your view: “A Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. This is the only truth, other ideas are silly”?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:50.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:50.4"
msgid "‘etampi kho, āvuso, bhagavatā abyākataṃ: "
msgstr "‘This too has not been declared by the Buddha.’ "

msgctxt "dn29:50.5"
msgid "“neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan”’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs51, sc51
msgctxt "dn29:51.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "The wanderers might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:51.2"
msgid "‘kasmā panetaṃ, āvuso, samaṇena gotamena abyākatan’ti? "
msgstr "‘But why has this not been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:51.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:51.4"
msgid "‘na hetaṃ, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ na dhammasaṃhitaṃ na ādibrahmacariyakaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, tasmā taṃ bhagavatā abyākatan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Because it’s not beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. That’s why it hasn’t been declared by the Buddha.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:51.5"
msgid "14. Byākataṭṭhāna "
msgstr "14. The Declared Points "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs52, sc52
msgctxt "dn29:52.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that wanderers who follow other paths might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:52.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāvuso, samaṇena gotamena byākatan’ti? "
msgstr "‘But what has been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:52.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:52.4"
msgid "‘idaṃ dukkhanti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhasamudayoti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhanirodhoti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā byākataṃ, ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadāti kho, āvuso, bhagavatā byākatan’ti. "
msgstr "‘What has been declared by the Buddha is this: “This is suffering”—“This is the origin of suffering”—“This is the cessation of suffering”—“This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering.”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs53, pts-vp-pli3.137, sc53
msgctxt "dn29:53.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, cunda, vijjati, yaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "The wanderers might say, "

msgctxt "dn29:53.2"
msgid "‘kasmā panetaṃ, āvuso, samaṇena gotamena byākatan’ti? "
msgstr "‘But why has this been declared by the ascetic Gotama?’ "

msgctxt "dn29:53.3"
msgid "Evaṃvādino, cunda, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evamassu vacanīyā: "
msgstr "You should say to them, "

msgctxt "dn29:53.4"
msgid "‘etañhi, āvuso, atthasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ dhammasaṃhitaṃ, etaṃ ādibrahmacariyakaṃ ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati. Tasmā taṃ bhagavatā byākatan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Because it’s beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the spiritual life. It leads to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. That’s why it has been declared by the Buddha.’ "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn29:53.5"
msgid "15. Pubbantasahagatadiṭṭhinissaya "
